look.title: Top Downloaded Clicks
look.description: A table of Download File, Download count, and percent of total downloads, ordered by Download Count.

dashboard_elements.note_text: A Download click shows the count that users have clicked to download an asset linked to on your page.
dashboard_elements.note_text_as_html: A Download click shows the count that users have clicked to download an asset linked to on your page.

look.title: Top Offsite Links
look.description: A table of Offsite Link, and count of clicks ordered by clicks descending.

dashboard_elements.note_text: An Offsite link click on your page is a click on a URL link that does not contain the domain "www2.gov.bc.ca".
dashboard_elements.note_text_as_html: An Offsite link click on your page is a click on a URL link that does not contain the domain "www2.gov.bc.ca".

look.title: Top Referrer URL Hosts
look.description:
A clustered bar graph showing referrers with a session count dimension and a percent of referrals dimension, ordered by session count descending.

Note: this version uses the Page Views table. For the sessions version see: https://analytics.gov.bc.ca/looks/290

dashboard_elements.note_text:
Users landing on the website/web page from other websites, search engines, etc.

If you see this result "statics.teams.cdn.office.net", the referrer is coming from a Microsoft Teams environment. For example, you shared the website link in a Teams chat, and folks are clicking on that link.

look.title: Page Views by Traffic Channel
look.description:
A stacked bar graph of referrals by medium (email, internal, search, social, unknown, or NULL). 

Requires a page view start date filter to return results.

Note: This is the page views version, for the sessions version see: https://analytics.gov.bc.ca/looks/275

dashboard_elements.note_text: An indicator of where traffic to the website/web page comes from. Traffic channels are separated into a number of groups. For details about the different traffic channels, please visit the Glossary.
dashboard_elements.note_text_as_html: An indicator of where traffic to the website/web page comes from. Traffic channels are separated into a number of groups. For details about the different traffic channels, please visit the Glossary.

dashboard_elements.note_text: A chart displaying the Sub Themes of a theme based on the number of Google.com Impressions and Google.com Clicks.
dashboard_elements.note_text_as_html: A chart displaying the Sub Themes of a theme based on the number of Google.com Impressions and Google.com Clicks.

look.title: Top Gov Search Terms
look.description: A table of Search Term and Search Count ordered by Search Count.

dashboard_elements.note_text: Displays the phrases and the number of its searches within the BC government search box which led the user to a page within a theme.
dashboard_elements.note_text_as_html: Displays the phrases and the number of its searches within the BC government search box which led the user to a page within a theme.

dashboard_elements.note_text:
These are the most common URLs that are directing users to your site. It is ordered by page views count and shows the percentage of page views from this referral URL. 

The null results symbol () are results from direct traffic (someone clicks on a bookmark or someone types in or copies and pastes the URL directly in a browser). In some instances, results may not have been trackable.

If you see a result containing this "statics.teams.cdn.office.net", the referrer is coming from a Microsoft Teams environment. For example, you shared the website link in a Teams chat, and folks are clicking on that link.
